shows.title: #O2LForever
shows.overview: Join Connor Franta, Jc Caylen, Kian Lawley, Ricky Dillon, Sam Pottorff and Trevor Moran as the YouTube supergroup Our 2nd Life (O2L) embarks upon their 2014 North American tour. Step inside their journey, from blogging in their bedrooms to performing in front of screaming fans across the country. This 95-minute adventure captures their launch into the next level of stardom while they try to stay grounded and maintain authentic connections with the communities that started it all.

shows.title: (Romance) in the Digital Age
shows.overview: When the video of a once-famous emo band performing karaoke goes viral, a door opens for a possible reunion at the guitarist’s Christmas wedding.

shows.title: (Untitled)
shows.overview: The proprietor of a trendy art gallery in New York City becomes enamored with a vibrant but moody music composer when their snooty social circles mix.

shows.title: 10,000 Saints
shows.overview: A teen from Vermont moves to live with his dad in New York’s East Village, where other youngsters and parents struggle to cope in the volatile 1980s.
Four connected stories explore the notion of love in a Singapore hotel and the extent some will go to in order to obtain it.

shows.title: Radio Pirates
shows.overview: Inspired by true events, a 23-year-old journalist fights to break the New Zealand government’s monopoly on broadcasting policy and usher in rock music.

shows.title: 1991: The Year Punk Broke
shows.overview: Take a trip with Sonic Youth and Nirvana as they stumble through their 1991 European club & festival tour!
A wannabe pop star, a flight attendant and a divorcée at different stages of their lives each chase their dreams and search for solace in Taipei.

shows.title: 20,000 Days on Earth
shows.overview: The acclaimed music documentary of Australian musician Nick Cave through lyrics, dream-like sequences, and a fresh take on the artistic process.

shows.title: 200 Motels
shows.overview: The great Frank Zappa's outrageous psychedelic precursor to today's music videos features "The Mothers of Invention" wreaking havoc in a typical American town. Ringo Starr narrates.

shows.title: Back to the 90s
shows.overview: After calling a number he found on his dad's old pager, a rebellious teen is instantly transported back to 1995, when his parents were his age.

shows.title: 27: Gone Too Soon
shows.overview: An examination of "The 27 Club,” made up of talented musicians who died before their time, often because of a fast and loose lifestyle.

shows.title: 33 Postcards
shows.overview: Dean Randall has sponsored a young Chinese orphan Mei Mei for many years, when she arrives in Sydney out of the blue to thank him, their lives are changed forever.

shows.title: 365 Nights in Hollywood
shows.overview: Down-on-his-luck film director Jimmie Dale takes a job at a fly-by-night acting school. He is drawn into the plans of the school's owner to bilk a wealthy young man out of funds.

shows.title: 48 Hours to Live
shows.overview: Fresh out of rehab and wanted by both sides of the law, Wyatt is seriously thinking about building a different kind of life for himself. But when his sister is murdered, he finds himself entangled in a game of revenge on the LA club circuit.

shows.title: 5 Seconds of Summer: How Did We End Up Here?
shows.overview: On the day of the release of their new album Youngblood, the boys of 5 Seconds of Summer played an intimate, one-night-only gig for fans in New York City. Interspersed with some stage banter from several of the members, this live set sees the band run through album cuts such as "Moving Along" and "Valentine" as well as past fan favorites like "She Looks So Perfect."
